hotographers-waterfalls-800x533.jpg 800w, https://www.slrlounge.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/photographers-waterfalls-750x500.jpg 750w, https://www.slrlounge.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/photographers-waterfalls-585x390.jpg 585w, https://www.slrlounge.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/photographers-waterfalls-525x350.jpg 525w, https://www.slrlounge.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/photographers-waterfalls-400x267.jpg 400w, https://www.slrlounge.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/photographers-waterfalls-306x204.jpg 306w, https://www.slrlounge.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/photographers-waterfalls-200x133.jpg 200w, https://www.slrlounge.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/photographers-waterfalls-100x67.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.slrlounge.com/7-waterfall-photography-tips-to-expand-your-creative-vision/" data-jpibfi-post-title="7 Waterfall Photography Tips to Expand Your Creative Vision" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.slrlounge.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/photographers-waterfalls-750x500.jpg" ></noscript><span class="c8 c12">Photo by</span><span class="c8 c13"><a class="c1" href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.pexels.com/@lucasallmann?utm_content%3DattributionCopyText%26utm_medium%3Dreferral%26utm_source%3Dpexels&amp;sa=D&amp;ust=1598992131116000&amp;usg=AOvVaw1agipl9AjYvgEDk9u1verq">Lucas Allmann</a></span><span class="c12 c8">from</span><span class="c13 c8"><a class="c1" href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.pexels.com/photo/cascade-daylight-environment-forest-448754/?utm_content%3DattributionCopyText%26utm_medium%3Dreferral%26utm_source%3Dpexels&amp;sa=D&amp;ust=1598992131116000&amp;usg=AOvVaw3KK5xzyRU6XOw-mTDzZCac">Pexels</a></span></p>
<p>Probably the most overlooked advice when it comes to waterfall photography tips is the importance of preparing your kit and wearing the right clothes. Even small waterfalls can produce spray or splashes that can hit your lens, so it makes sense to bring lots of lens cloths to dry your lens and filters and to have a waterproof camera bag.</p>
<p>You should wear waterproofs and boots with a decent sole that are capable of gripping on slippery wet rocks, and an umbrella is also an option for using between shots, but you may find it too cumbersome.</p>
<h3 class="c7"><span class="c5">7. Visit in Different Seasons</span></h3>
<p class="c4" style="text-align: center;"><img class="lazy lazy-hidden aligncenter size-full wp-image-880916" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-lazy-type="image" data-lazy-src="https://www.slrlounge.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/winter-waterfalls-749x500.jpg" alt="winter waterfalls" width="700" height="467" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.slrlounge.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/winter-waterfalls.jpg 1950w, https://www.slrlounge.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/winter-waterfalls-800x534.jpg 800w, https://www.slrlounge.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/winter-waterfalls-749x500.jpg 749w, https://www.slrlounge.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/winter-waterfalls-585x390.jpg 585w, https://www.slrlounge.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/winter-waterfalls-525x350.jpg 525w, https://www.slrlounge.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/winter-waterfalls-400x267.jpg 400w, https://www.slrlounge.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/winter-waterfalls-306x204.jpg 306w, https://www.slrlounge.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/winter-waterfalls-200x133.jpg 200w, https://www.slrlounge.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/winter-waterfalls-1600x1067.jpg 1600w, https://www.slrlounge.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/winter-waterfalls-100x67.jpg 100w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.slrlounge.com/7-waterfall-photography-tips-to-expand-your-creative-vision/" data-jpibfi-post-title="7 Waterfall Photography Tips to Expand Your Creative Vision" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.slrlounge.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/winter-waterfalls-749x500.jpg" ><noscript><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-880916" src="https://www.slrlounge.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/winter-waterfalls-749x500.jpg" alt="winter waterfalls" width="700" height="467" srcset="https://www.slrlounge.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/winter-waterfalls.jpg 1950w, https://www.slrlounge.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/winter-waterfalls-800x534.jpg 800w, https://www.slrlounge.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/winter-waterfalls-749x500.jpg 749w, https://www.slrlounge.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/winter-waterfalls-585x390.jpg 585w, https://www.slrlounge.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/winter-waterfalls-525x350.jpg 525w, https://www.slrlounge.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/winter-waterfalls-400x267.jpg 400w, https://www.slrlounge.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/winter-waterfalls-306x204.jpg 306w, https://www.slrlounge.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/winter-waterfalls-200x133.jpg 200w, https://www.slrlounge.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/winter-waterfalls-1600x1067.jpg 1600w, https://www.slrlounge.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/winter-waterfalls-100x67.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.slrlounge.com/7-waterfall-photography-tips-to-expand-your-creative-vision/" data-jpibfi-post-title="7 Waterfall Photography Tips to Expand Your Creative Vision" data-jpibfi-src="https://www.slrlounge.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/winter-waterfalls-749x500.jpg" ></noscript><img class="lazy lazy-hidden" title="" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-lazy-type="image" data-lazy-src="images/image1.jpg" alt="" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.slrlounge.com/7-waterfall-photography-tips-to-expand-your-creative-vision/" data-jpibfi-post-title="7 Waterfall Photography Tips to Expand Your Creative Vision" data-jpibfi-src="images/image1.jpg" ><noscript><img title="" src="images/image1.jpg" alt="" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://www.slrlounge.com/7-waterfall-photography-tips-to-expand-your-creative-vision/" data-jpibfi-post-title="7 Waterfall Photography Tips to Expand Your Creative Vision" data-jpibfi-src="images/image1.jpg" ></noscript>Photo by <a href="https://unsplash.com/@trevcole?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText">Trevor Cole</a> on <a href="https://unsplash.com/s/photos/winter-waterfall?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText">Unsplash</a></p>
<p class="c7"><span class="c3">The final one of our waterfall photography tips is to visit the same waterfall in different seasons, as they take on a diverse range of looks according to the time of year you visit. If youre lucky, the waterfall may even freeze solid in winter, giving a stunning display of icicles.</span></p>
<h3>Conclusion</h3>
<p>Waterfalls open up a world of creativity for landscape photographers. Whether you&#8217;re a beginner just starting out or an advanced seasoned pro, the most important tip we can give you is to just get out there and shoot! The photos are almost always worth the early mornings, long hikes, and challenging environments! What other tips do you have for photographing waterfalls? Let us know your thoughts in the comments!</p>

